PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FIt also follows Greater Manchester
OL,8,FMayor Andy Burnham's announcement that
OL,9,Fhe intends to fight the Makerfield by-
OL,10,Felection.
OL,12,FMr Burnham has said a vote for him
OL,13,Fwould be a vote to "change Labour",
OL,14,Fwhile Sir Keir has insisted he will
OL,15,Fnot set out a timetable for his
OL,16,Fdeparture even if the mayor returns to
OL,17,FParliament.
OL,26,@uD@TOUuD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FIf Sir Keir does not resign, Mr
OL,8,FBurnham would need to secure the
OL,9,Fbacking of 81 Labour MPs to mount a
OL,10,Fleadership challenge, potentially
OL,11,Fsetting up a contest with the Prime
OL,12,FMinister for party members' votes.
OL,14,FBut on Monday evening, one of his
OL,15,Fsupporters suggested the mayor would
OL,16,Fnot seek an immediate leadership fight.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FLeeds MP Alex Sobel told LBC it was
OL,8,Fnot his "expectation" that Mr Burnham
OL,9,Fwould immediately trigger a contest,
OL,10,Fsaying he would "come back and
OL,11,Fpotentially serve in the Government,
OL,12,Ftry and help us turn this Government
OL,13,Fround".
OL,15,FMeanwhile, polling by YouGov suggested
OL,16,FMr Burnham would be Labour members'
OL,17,Fpreferred candidate for leader, with
OL,18,F47% saying he would be their first
OL,19,Fchoice for the job.
OL,26,@pD@IOUpD@UO]rD@QOUuD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FSome 31% ranked Sir Keir as their
OL,8,Ffirst choice, followed by former
OL,9,Fdeputy prime minister Angela Rayner on
OL,10,F8%.
OL,12,FJust 4% ranked Mr Streeting as their
OL,13,Ffirst choice, with 57% saying he was
OL,14,Fwrong to resign as health secretary
OL,15,Fand 15% backing him in a head-to-head
OL,16,Fcontest with the Prime Minister.
OL,18,FIn a contest between Mr Burnham and
OL,19,FSir Keir, 59% said they would back the
OL,20,Fmayor while 37% would support the
OL,21,FPrime Minister.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FAmid continued leadership speculation,
OL,8,FMr Burnham is also likely to face
OL,9,Ffurther pressure to set out his stall
OL,10,Ffor Labour members.
OL,12,FOn Monday, the mayor said he wanted to
OL,13,Fsee more power devolved to local
OL,14,Fareas, complaining of a "bloated
OL,15,Fnational state" and a "malnourished
OL,16,Flocal one".
OL,26,@vD@YOUwD@OO]wD@WOUxD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779152632
OL,3,CKeir Starmer to chair first Cabinet
OL,4,Cmeeting since Wes Streeting's
OL,5,Cresignation
OL,7,FBut he also appeared to row back on
OL,8,Fprevious comments on the EU, saying he
OL,9,Fwas "not proposing that the UK
OL,10,Fconsiders rejoining" the bloc and
OL,11,Fwarning against rerunning the
OL,12,Farguments of the Brexit years.
OL,14,FMr Burnham has previously said he
OL,15,Fwanted to see the UK back in the EU
OL,16,Fwithin his lifetime.
OL,26,@qD@EOUrD@TO]
